{
  "stem": "22840.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father wanted her to do that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He told her, don't stay in this bloody-- this land full of blood.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He may have.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But his views about that place were very clear.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's a place of blood, and crime, and hatred.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Still today, with the exception of people like Anna and Maria Baluhova, which I think are-- are the minority.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "These are people from the very, very small villages.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This-- this-- this-- the people in the village in Buly, I don't know if they knew what money is.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was all like barter.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Barter economy, where they swapped shoes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I told you I was-- I was helping this guy to make the-- the-- the thread for the pelt shoes, and he was swapping the shoes for other things.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't think it was the money based community.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Those people were humans.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Others just hated.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What-- what happened is Palestine-- it was not-- it was before the structure, before they started.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was the mandate.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was under the mandate of United Nations.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a mandate of the pre-United Nations.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The-- I don't know how it's called-- how the-- that organization was called.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After the Second World War, there was an organization, how it was called-- it was not called United Nations.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was-- I know in Hebrew it's called differently than the United Nations.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In Hebrew, it's called [HEBREW], which is the Organization of Nations, or-- or the Brotherhood of Nations.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know what the official English name of that organization was.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "British were given mandate over that part of the world, which continued throughout the war.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the British were in control.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The British would not let Jews come in, except in limited numbers.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
